title: Review: ‘Midnights’ Finds Taylor Swift Between Yesterday and Tomorrow
description: The singer-songwriter’s 10th studio album returns to the pop sound she left in 2019, and explores a familiar subject: how she is perceived, and how she perceives herself.
dc:creator: Jon Caramanica
media:description: Taylor Swift’s “Midnights” recalls the sound of “Lover,” the album she put out in 2019 before two surprise releases — “Folklore” and “Evermore” — in 2020.
